title: Wrong data set result returned when an invalid filter expression is set for row[0]
description: When setting a filter expression like "row[0] equals to 0", the result set is not returned correctly. Instead, a null result set is returned. An error message should be displayed when an invalid filter expression is set.
OB: When setting the filter expression "row[0] equals to 0", the result set is not returned correctly.
EB: Instead of returning the correct result set, a null result set is returned. Additionally, an error message should be displayed when an invalid filter expression is set.
SR:
To reproduce the issue: 
1. Set an invalid filter expression like "row[0] equals to 0"
2. Verify that the result set is not returned correctly
3. Make sure that an error message is displayed when an invalid filter expression is set
